Okay, now onto my cliché for the day: Leader pictures made in piccrew or taken out of some flash visual novel. I've seen this trope in use heavily and while some people do well on it (E.G: Khoronzon or whatever with Emperor Narcissus) because after they do the picture they embellish it further via photo editing, others just leave the picture as is without even taking out the background or even the link to the flash game website. I always go somewhere along the lines of: Bro what in the bloody hell of cringe is this.

I'm somewhat guilty of this trope as well, with my either The Sims or FIFA generated characters. But at least I go through the trouble of making it up with consistent writing, characterization, and editing the damn pictures to take the background out if where they stand don't make sense.
